This section provides information for contributing to the Asmeta and to use it to develop new tools. 


The project is now hosted on the github platform, its overview page is [https://github.com/asmeta](https://github.com/asmeta)

You can submit [issues](https://github.com/asmeta/asmeta/issues).


### Repository Organisation

* under code there is the source code. In core all the basic projects. Under extensions all the tools we have built and are now part of asmeta.


### Working with the Asmeta sources
The better way is to use eclipse and checkout the projects from the git.
